<subSubSection id="33CB651CFFBFFFFF5BE9FADDE618FA6D" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7B6E3697FFBFFFFF5BE9FADDE618FA6D" blockId="30.[192,1441,291,1691]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5BE9FADDE6C1FA8D" bold="true" box="[240,397,1379,1403]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name means “handsome or imposing” and refers to this species’ large size and bright color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33CB651CFFBFFFFF5BE9FA1DE3D1FA4D" box="[240,1181,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7B6E3697FFBFFFFF5BE9FA1DE3D1FA4D" blockId="30.[192,1441,291,1691]" box="[240,1181,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5BE9FA1DE53AFA4D" bold="true" box="[240,630,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Distribution and phenology.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="A46A8835FFBFFFFF5F32FA1DE3D5FA4D" box="[1067,1177,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33CB651CFFBFFFFF5BE9FA7DE43EF96D" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7B6E3697FFBFFFFF5BE9FA7DE43EF96D" blockId="30.[192,1441,291,1691]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5BE9FA7DE51FFA2D" bold="true" box="[240,595,1475,1499]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis and discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5940FA7DE4C9FA2D" authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[601,901,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5940FA7DE4C9FA2D" box="[601,901,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Porphyrogenes speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the larger species of the genus. The valva, especially the long and upcurved harpe, of 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5801FA5AE4E5FA0D" authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[792,937,1508,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5801FA5AE4E5FA0D" box="[792,937,1508,1531]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to this structure of 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5E08FA5AE235FA0D" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1297,1401,1508,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stresa">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5E08FA5AE235FA0D" box="[1297,1401,1508,1531]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. stresa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5E9EFA5AE648F9ED" baseAuthorityName="Moschler" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zohra">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5E9EFA5AE648F9ED" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. zohra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5A5DF9BAE6FFF9ED" authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[324,435,1540,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sparus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5A5DF9BAE6FFF9ED" box="[324,435,1540,1563]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. sparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the costa-ampulla is broader and more quadrate than on any of those species. In addition, the uncus of 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5AD7F99AE513F9CD" authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[462,607,1572,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5AD7F99AE513F9CD" box="[462,607,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer than on those species. The valva of 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5F66F99AE39FF9CD" box="[1151,1235,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sula">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5F66F99AE39FF9CD" box="[1151,1235,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. sula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="1F404B66FFBFFFFF5BD9F9FDE6B5F9AD" author="Williams, R. C., Jr. &amp; E. L. Bell" box="[192,505,1603,1627]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" pagination="121 - 140" refId="ref37020" refString="Williams, R. C., Jr., and E. L. Bell. 1940. New Neotropical Hesperiidae and notes on others (Lepidoptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 66: 121 - 140." type="journal article" year="1940">Williams and Bell (1940)</bibRefCitation>
is somewhat quadrate as on 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5875F9FAE34DF9AD" authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[876,1025,1604,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5875F9FAE34DF9AD" box="[876,1025,1604,1627]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the harpe appears similarly expanded near its bend. 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFBFFFFF5AFAF9DDE582F98D" box="[483,718,1635,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sula">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFBFFFFF5AFAF9DDE582F98D" box="[483,718,1635,1659]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Porphyrogenes sula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, is smaller, has different venation and wing shape, and has blackish tufts anteriorly on the dorsal hindwing;
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
